name: THE LIMINAL SPACE : ARCHIVED
description:
THE LIMINAL SPACE :ARCHIVED 

This piece was heavily influenced by the song Smothered by Daughter when working on this piece. The line "I wish I had stayed inside my mother and never to come out" haunted me back when i was developing the drafts of The Liminal Space. 

Liminal space exists when physical experience meets the internal dialogue. An ever evolving space for one to comprehend the present time and its embodiment in many forms.
